The paper deals with algorithmic problems related to graph structures and their width measures, such as clique-width, rank-width, and maximum induced matching width. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). However, given the focus on graph structures and connectivity/acyclicity constraints, cs.DS and cs.DM seem to be the most likely categories. The other categories are also possible, as they deal with related topics such as computational complexity and graph theory.
